gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 127, Raptors 107
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers defeated the Raptors, 127-107 as they win their fourth straight game to improve to 29-14. James Harden led the Clippers with the 75th triple-double of his career and his first of the season (22 points, 10 rebounds,  13 assists) as Paul George (21 points) and Russell Westbrook (20 points, five rebounds, three assists) totaled 41 points. Scottie Barnes (23 points, five rebounds, four assists) and RJ Barrett (22 points, six rebounds, four assists) led the Raptors. The Raptors move to 16-29 with the loss.
